value.value: Aumento del nivel de glutarilglicina en orina

definition.value: The amount of glutarylglycine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de indican en orina

Detection of indican in the urine. Urinary indican concentration may be elevated in small bowel bacterial overgrowth. Indican is produced by bacterial deconjugation of dietary tryptophan to indole which is absorbed at all levels of the intestine, but principally from the small bowel.
Dacrolito
Dacryolith is a concretion (accumulation of sediment) within the nasolacrimal system.

definition.value: Dacryoliths may cause intermittent epiphora without inflammation, or recurrent dacryocystitis may develop.

value.value: Activity of gamma-glutamylcysteine synthetase (EC 6.3.2.2) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Decreased erythrocyte nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide-cytochrome b5 reductase activity

value.value: Disminución de la actividad circulante de la nicotinamida adenina dinucleótido-citocromo b5 reductasa

value.value: The activity of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH)-cytochrome b5 reductase in erythrocytes (red blood cells) is below the lower limit of normal.
Disminución de la actividad de la alfa-metilacil-CoA racemasa en fibroblastos cultivados

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Reduced alpha-methylacyl-CoA racemase activity in cultured fibroblasts

label.value: Reduced alpha-methylacyl-CoA racemase activity in cultured fibroblasts

value.value: Activity of alpha-methylacyl-CoA racemase (AMACR; EC 5.1.99.4) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.
Bajo volumen del semen

definition.value: Volume of semen in ejaculate below the lower limit of normal. This finding can be ascertained by semen analysis. Comment: Sperm are produced within the testis, in the process of spermatogenesis, then travel through the male reproductive tract (the seminiferous tubules, epididymis, vas deferens, prostate and urethra). As the sperm travel, seminal fluid is added from the seminal vesicles, prostate, testis and epididymis and periurethral glands. The function of the ejaculate is to transport sperm into the female genital tract and to provide a suitable environment for sperm survival during this transit.

value.value: Localizado en el codo.

definition.value: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the elbow.

value.value: Lúnula agrandada
Abnormal enlargement of the visible portion of the distal nail matrix that extends beyond the proximal nail fold, which is referred to as the lunula.
Localizado en el talón

definition.value: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the heel.

value.value: Hemorragias en astilla
Thin, red to reddish-brown lines of blood (hemorrhages) under the nails. Splinter hemorrhages run vertically under the nails.

definition.value: Splinter hemorrhages represent rupture of longitudinally oriented nail plate capillaries leading to extravasation and the historical hallmark of linear discoloration. See figure 1 of PMID:36050132.

value.value: Empuje lateral

Lateral thrust (LT) refers to an abnormal knee joint motion in the early stance phase where the knee joint center moves laterally. Also known as varus thrust, LR is defined as the dynamic worsening or abrupt onset of varus (bow-leg) alignment as the limb accepts weight (stance phase), with a return to less varus and more neutral alignment during lift-off and the non-weight-bearing (swing) phase of gait, varus thrust is a potent mechanical risk factor for medial knee osteoarthritis progression.

definition.value: LT visualized during walking is associated with a greater medial knee load and an increased risk of medial knee osteoarthritis (OA) progression.

value.value: Contusión cerebral

A contusion is a region of injured tissue in which blood capillaries have been ruptured without laceration (bruise). Brain contusions are bruises of the cortical surface that damage the surface from the outside inward, producing disruption of tissue and vessels. The term cerebral contusion describes the pathology of focal necrosis and hemorrhage, typically observed in older children, involving particularly cerebral cortex and subcortical white matter. Such lesions are usually found in coup and contrecoup, as well as inferior orbital, frontal, and temporal locations. Cerebral contusions cause permanent damage to tissues of the cerebrum. The etiology of cerebral contusion is trauma to the head.

definition.value: Cerebral contusion is the classic example of focal traumatic brain injury (TBI). In the pre-CT era, cerebral contusion could be diagnosed only in the operating room during craniotomy or at the autopsy table. Initially, the CT may show isodense or hypodense areas, sometimes mixed-density lesions commonly surrounded by perilesional hypodense areas, but later more surrounding edema with progression over time. Multiple focal contusions may have a salt and pepper appearance. The bone window is used for the evaluation of skull fractures. Brain magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) is not indicated in the acute management of TBI. If acutely done, there are isointense to hyperintense areas on T1-weighted images and hyperintense on T2-weighted images. Fluid-attenuated inversion recovery images demonstrate petechial hemorrhages that are isointense to the brain. The MRI can show ischemic areas and changes from diffuse axonal injury. It can be used later for cognitive problems.

value.value: Fecolito
A mass of accumulated hardened fecal matter.
Apendicitis
Appendicitis is inflammation of the vermiform appendix. Appendix a hollow organ located at the tip of the cecum, usually in the right lower quadrant of the abdomen.
Aneurisma ventricular izquierdo
A severely scarred portion of infarcted ventricular myocardium that does not contract normally but instead bulges outward while the rest of the ventricle contracts during systole.

definition.value: A left ventricular aneurysm is one of the worst complications after acute myocardial infarction. The natural course leading to the formation of a ventricular aneurysm involves a full-thickness infarct that has been replaced by fibrous tissue. This inert portion cannot take part in the contraction and herniates outward during systole. Most of the LV aneurysms are asymptomatic and are found in follow-up echocardiography. However, large symptomatic LV aneurysms can cause heart failure, ventricular tachyarrhythmias, and sudden cardiac death.

value.value: Silueta cardíaca en forma de bota

definition.value: An abnormal form of the heart seen upon chest radiography in which the heart displays an upturned apex and slight concave pulmonary artery segment. This configuration is said to resemble a boot.

value.value: Hidrosálpinx
Hydrosalpinx is a distension or dilatation of the fallopian tube in the presence of a distal tubal occlusion.

definition.value: The most common cause of hydrosalpinx is pelvic inflammatory disease.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de metilhex-dienodioico por espectrometría de resonancia magnética
An increase in the level of 3-methylhex-2,4-dienedioic acid or 3-methylhex-3,4-dienedioic acid in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).
Realce perihepático
Increased signal (contrast enhancement) surrounding the liver observed on computer tomography or magnetic resonance imaging following administration of contrast agents.

definition.value: See figure 2 of PMID:35528764.

value.value: Disminución del umbral de la prueba de contractura in vitro

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Reduced in vitro contracture test threshold

label.value: Reduced in vitro contracture test threshold

value.value: The in vitro contracture test determines the sensitivity of freshly obtained skeletal muscle specimens to caffeine or halothane applied to a bathing solution. Muscles from persons susceptible to malignant hyperthermia have lower contracture thresholds for these agents than do normal muscle.
Disminución de la amplitud de la onda F
Reduced strength (amplitude) of the F-wave, which is an electrophysiological artifact produced by antidromic activation of motoneurons following distal electrical stimulation of motor nerve fibers.

definition.value: Because F-waves traverse the entire length of a peripheral nerve between the spinal cord and muscle, F-waves provide a means of examining transmission between stimulation sites in the arm and the leg and the related motoneurons in the cervical and lumbosacral cord. The F-wave is so named because it was originally studied in the small muscles of the foot. It is one of several responses that may follow the direct motor (M) response evoked by electrical stimulation of mixed or motor nerves.

value.value: Peroxisomas agrandados
Abnormal increase in size of peroxisomes.

definition.value: See figure 2 of PMID:2894756.

value.value: Hiperplasia de la cortical suprarrenal

A non-malignant growth, or enlargement, of the adrenal glands, specifically the cortex, although the cortex cannot be definitively identified by conventional imaging. Adrenal cortical hyperplasia is defined radiologically as a non-malignant growth, or enlargement, of the adrenal glands.

definition.value: Controlled by the pituitary gland, the adrenal cortex drives critical processes, such as the production of cortisol, mineralocorticoid and sex hormones. Any disruption in the multiple enzymes and hormones involved in these pathways may cause serious or life-threatening symptoms, often associated with anatomical changes in the adrenal glands.

value.value: Infiltración linfocítica de la glándula parótida.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Lymphocytic infiltration of the parotid gland

label.value: Lymphocytic infiltration of the parotid gland

definition.value: Accumulation of lymphocytes in the parotid gland. This feature is generally defined as a count of lymphocytes per area that is above normal limits on histopathological examination.

value.value: Granuloma de médula ósea

A granuloma (a focal aggregate of immune cells that forms in response to a persistent inflammatory stimulus) localiyed to the bone marrow. A granuloma characteristically demonstrates the compact organization of mature macrophages, which may or may not be associated with other inflammatory cell types.
Cuerpos de inclusión intranucleares neuronales.
The presence of intracellular inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in neurons.
Atrofia pancreática
Wasting (shrinking) of the pancreas.

definition.value: Pancreatic atrophy is commonly seen in elderly patients and may also be a sequela of conditions including chronic pancreatitis, cystic fibrosis, and Shwachman-Bodian-Diamond syndrome.

value.value: Disminución de la densidad de células acinares pancreáticas.
Number (count) of pancreatic acinar cells reduced below normal. This feature can be ascertained by pancreas biopsy.
Acumulación de colesterol no esterificado en fibroblastos cultivados.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Unesterified cholesterol accumulation in cultured fibroblasts

label.value: Unesterified cholesterol accumulation in cultured fibroblasts

value.value: An abnormal result of the the filipin test. In this test is based on the reaction of unesterified cholesterol with fluorescent antibiotic filipin giving a strongly fluorescent, stable cholesterol-filipin complex suitable for in situ detection. An abnormal test result is present if there is a perinuclear accumulation of staining in lysosomal storage organelles (LSOs).

definition.value: The filipin test is useful for the evaluation of impaired cholesterol esterification in cultured cells (fibroblasts or others) in Niemann-Pick disease type C.

value.value: Infiltración hepática de macrófagos cargados de lípidos
Accumulation of foamy cells (lipid-laden macrophages) in the parenchyma of the liver.

definition.value: See figure 2 of PMID:17939344.

value.value: Infiltración esplénica de macrófagos cargados de lípidos
Accumulation of foamy cells (lipid-laden macrophages) in the parenchyma of the spleen.
Reducción de la actividad de la N-acetilglutamato sintasa hepática
Concentration or activity of N-acetylglutamate synthase in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal.
Consumo excesivo de regaliz
Ingestion of large amounts of licorice.

definition.value: Licorice is a popular sweetener found in many soft drinks, food products, snacks and herbal medicines. Licorice toxicity is characterized by the symptom triad of hypertension, hypokalemia, and metabolic alkalosis, so-called pseudohyperaldosteronism. The active ingredient in licorice is glycyrrhizin, which is converted to 3beta-monoglucuronyl-18beta-glycyrrhetinic acid (3MGA) and 18beta-glycyrrhetinic acid (GA) in the gut. These active metabolites inhibit the 11beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase type II enzyme and prevent the conversion of cortisol to cortisone. Unlike cortisone, cortisol binds to the mineralocorticoid receptor. This cortisol excess leads to increased potassium and proton excretion as well as to sodium and water retention, with increased systemic resistance. The triad of symptoms typical of classic hyperaldosteronism (Conn syndrome) results from the aldosterone-like effect: hypokalemia, hypertension, and metabolic alkalosis.

value.value: Localizado en el hombro

definition.value: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the shoulder.

value.value: Embarazo concebido a pesar del dispositivo intrauterino

Intrauterine devices (IUDs) are used for contraception. Rarely pregnancy occurs despite the presence of an IUD. Such pregnancies are associated with an increased risk of spontaneous abortion and preterm delivery due to infection, and a higher risk of maternal septic complications.
Deficiencia materna de folato
The mother of a fetus or index patient has a history of folate deficiency during the corresponding pregnancy.
Deficiencia materna de zinc
The mother of a fetus or index patient has a history of abnormally low zinc levels during the corresponding pregnancy.

definition.value: Maternal zinc deficiency may increase the risk low birth weight (LBW) and small for gestational age (SGA) infants.

value.value: Uso de dispositivo intrauterino
Intrauterine devices (IUD) are commonly used for contraception. IUD complications are rare, but include perforation, pelvic infection, expulsion, missing strings, and difficult IUD removal.
Antecedente de catéter venoso central reciente

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: History of recent central venous catheter

label.value: History of recent central venous catheter

value.value: A past medical history of a recent central venous catheter (CVC). A CVC is an indwelling device inserted into a large, central vein (most commonly the internal jugular, subclavian, or femoral) and advanced until the terminal lumen resides within the inferior vena cava, superior vena cava, or right atrium. CVCs can be a necessary producre for critically ill patients with indications such as total parenteral nutrition administration, dialysis, plasmapheresis, medication administration, and hemodynamic monitoring, and to facilitate further complex interventions such as transvenous pacemaker placement. Complications include arrhythmia, central vein stenosis, and sepsis.
Antecedente de dependencia total de nutrición parenteral

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: History of total parenteral nutrition dependence

label.value: History of total parenteral nutrition dependence

value.value: A past medical history of a recent depence on total parenteral nutrition (TPN), which refers to intravenously administered nutrition being the only source of nutrition the patient is receiving.
Dolor aliviado por la elevación de los testículos
This refers to testicular pain that is lessened or made more bearable by elevation of the testicle.

definition.value: Prehn sign, the relief of pain with the elevation of the testis, may be elicited in patients with epididymitis, although this is not a reliable finding.

value.value: Masa en la pared abdominal

An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to the abdominal wall (the skin, fascia, and muscle encases the abdominal cavity and viscera). The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.
Abultamiento de la membrana timpánica
The tympanic membrane protrudes (swells outwards). This feature may be observed with otoscopy.

definition.value: See Figure 1 of PMID:24134083.

value.value: Dolor de oído exacerbado al manipular el trago o el pabellón auricular.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Ear pain exacerbated by manipulating tragus or pinna

label.value: Ear pain exacerbated by manipulating tragus or pinna

definition.value: Applies to pain of the ear that is worsened, aggravated, or exacerbated by touching or moving the tragus or pinna.

value.value: Masa lateral del cuello

definition.value: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized to the side of the neck. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

value.value: Localización occipital

definition.value: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in the occiput (back part of the head).

value.value: Edema anterior del cuello

definition.value: Abormal enlargement of the front part of the neck owing to accumulation of fluid.

value.value: Edema uvular

definition.value: Abnormal enlargement of the uvula related to an abnormal accumulation of fluid.

value.value: Drenaje purulento del conducto de Stensen

definition.value: Flow of pus (purulence) from the Stensen duct. The Stensen duct is also known as the parotid duct and is the route that saliva takes from the major salivary gland (parotid gland) to the mouth.
